COPS have recovered the white Quantum used during a robbery at a school on Monday. The vehicle was found abandoned near Viva Foundation Pre-School in Mamelodi, Tshwane, shortly after the robbery. A group of 19 international students and two professors were at the school at the time of the robbery. Provincial commissioner Lieutenant-General Elias Mawela has instructed a team of detectives to work around the clock to catch the suspects. “It’s alleged a group of no fewer than five armed suspects accosted the visitors and robbed them of personal belongings, including laptops, cellphones, cameras, passports, plane tickets, bags and cash in US dollars,” Gauteng police spokesman Brigadier Mathapelo Peters said. Mawela condemned the incident. Police have appealed to anyone with information about the incident to contact Mamelodi police or phone CrimeStop on 08600 10111.